<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-17T16:56:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-17T16:56:00-05:00" n="168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.21/278.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Thomson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-17T17:00:00-04:56">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>As a last resort, its opponents have instituted proceedings in the
                            Supreme Court to test the constitutionality of the law by which Congress
                            approved the treaty.* * * I do not consider that any importance whatever
                            should be attached to this surely fruitless attack. * * *</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>